<figureCitation id="42C82A30CC5CFFBFFF02E159FF3364F4" box="[151,251,888,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="1.[151,275,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[201,1375,365,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[201,1375,357,1854]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. terminalia of male Haplaxius species from the Dominican Republic. 1 – 3, H. cabrerensis, n. sp., holotype. Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 4 – 6, H. jamaicae (Kramer). Male terminalia in left lateral, right lateral, and ventral views, respectively. 7, H. crudus (Van Duzee). Habitus, dorsal view; af, “ anal flap ” of Kramer (abdominal segment X); ml, median lobe of pygofer (pyg); tri, diagnostic subtriangular projection. All images are of specimens from the Dominican Republic." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197881/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
